Phase 8.5 home-mode swap only overlaid a single chrome://slayzone-<panel>/
WebView on top of the full 10-region grid. Electron renders distinct
layout trees per tab type. This replaces the swap with a real mode
branch.

SlayzoneRegionContainer gains `LayoutMode {kTaskDetail,kHome,kOverlay}`
+ `SetLayoutMode`. kHome hides sidebar/taskheader/browserchrome/terminal
and collapses the mid SlayzoneSplitView to fraction=1.0 so the tasklist
(kanban) owns the full main-area width — structural match with the
Electron reference. kOverlay keeps the grid mounted so
SlayzoneOverlayManager can restore prior mode on close.

SlayzoneBrowserView tracks mode, exposes `SetLayoutMode`, and wraps
the Phase 8.5 `SetHomePanel` as a back-compat adapter (Mojo ShowHomePanel
still resolves). Added `--slayzone-layout-mode=home|task-detail|overlay`
CLI switch for the validation harness. Removed home_panel_webview_
(now redundant — kanban lives in the tasklist region directly).

Mojo: `LayoutHost.SetLayoutMode(LayoutMode)` + matching enum, mirrored
on both layout.mojom copies.

